@lguohan  Added a document which explains the relation between port isolation and bridge port isolation.
Added example configurations. Also added an attribute ACL action.
Please review.

In correlated mode, every packet that matches mirroring, is mirrored, no matter what the buffer status is. This eventually can cause back pressure, such as buffers filling up, or pause frames being generated for loseless traffic.

In independent mode (best effort), when a packet matches mirroring, there is a check on the relevant queue of the analyzer port - if there is space in the buffer, the packet is mirrored. if the buffer is full, the packet isn't mirrored

